Edgar Wilmar Froese (born 6 June 1944) is a German artist and electronic music pioneer, best known for founding the electronic music group, Tangerine Dream. Although his solo and group recordings prior to 2003 name him as "Edgar Froese", his solo albums from 2003 onward bear the artist name "Edgar W. Froese". Froese was born in Tilsit (Sovetsk), East Prussia, during World War II. He took piano lessons from the age of 12, and started playing guitar at 15. After showing an early aptitude for art, Froese enrolled at the Academy of the Arts in West Berlin to study painting and sculpture.

Feature:
1. Handâ€‘held Coil On Plug fast ignition tester, battery powered, with stable and professional performance.
2. Designed to easily and quickly determine whether the COP produces the proper spark for the plug.
3. It works by receiving the signal from the secondary ignition coil, and the test result is accurate and reliable.
4. Once the signal is received, the tester will determine whether the COP produces the correct amount of voltage and arc duration.
5. If the voltage is correct, the tester will beep and the red LED indicator will flash; if the arc duration is correct, the green LED will also flash.


Specification:
Item Type: Ignition Coil Tester
Material: ABS
Battery: CR2032 button battery, 120mAh (built-in)
How to Use:
1. Correctly connect the connector and sensor head to the tester
2. The induction head is aligned with the ignition coil to start working, and the working status of the ignition coil is judged according to the result of lighting

Test Results:
Red LED Light
Consistent, steady flashing and beeping indicates the COP is producing the correct amount of voltage.
No response or an inconsistent response indicates the COP is NOT producing the correct amount of voltage.
This may be caused by one of the following:
1.Fouled spark plug, or incorrect gaps
2.Damaged/corroded wires or connectors
3.Faulty coil or PCM

Green LED light
Consistent and steady flashing indicates the duration of the arc is correct.
No response or an inconsistent response indicates the duration of the arc is NOT correct.
This may be caused by one of the following:
1.Shorted windings inside the coil
2. Resistance or bad connections in the
3. primary / secondary connections
4. Faulty coil

column4: Uniquely designed wood bookmarks created from all natural, eco-friendly wood 100% Real Wood, each bookmark will have it's own Unique Grain Pattern Wood used from foresters who follow sustainable yield harvesting methods Size: 7" x 1.75" x 3/64" (178 mm x 44 mm x 1 mm) Ultra thin, and flexible Made in the USA The wood used to produce these bookmarks are free from chemicals, and upcycles the byproducts of logs from foresters who follow sustainable yield harvesting methods. The process to make these eco wood bookmarks ultra thin is more involved than merely carving or sawing. Slicing the wood thinly forms a thin layer of wood cut from a log. The primary difference with solid wood is that solid wood is sawn from a log which produces more waste than when cutting thinly. In other words, processing a log this way maximizes the added value that can be obtained from a log and produces less waste. All eco wood bookmarks are Made in the USA. The nature of the wood utilized in the creation of these items may produce minor variations in edging and sizing. Bookmarks may also have a slight color variation and their own unique grain pattern as they are created from 100% real wood. Product should be kept in dry environments as radical changes in humidity, wetness and moisture causes wood and wood products like paper to expand naturally and curl. Should this happen, simply bend it gently back in the opposite direction and put inside a book to flatten out. Like your book, store in dry and non-humid environments.
